265
00:20:48,587 --> 00:20:50,720
Kang Hee, while you're seeing a hotel heir…

266
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:54,753
Were you just standing by while Ah Reum
is dating an orphan who does hard labor?

267
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:05,653
I'm sorry.

268
00:21:18,253 --> 00:21:20,420
Mom, how can you say that?

269
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:22,953
You said that, Mom.

270
00:21:22,953 --> 00:21:26,253
You said you hate people
who hit others the most!

271
00:21:26,253 --> 00:21:28,620
How can you be like this?

272
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:30,387
Next time, I'm going to hit him.

273
00:21:30,387 --> 00:21:32,853
All of this is for you.

274
00:22:08,987 --> 00:22:11,320
Don't do that in the future.

275
00:22:12,720 --> 00:22:15,087
Only Ah Reum is having a hard time.

276
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:20,687
You…

277
00:22:22,287 --> 00:22:24,320
Do you want to go to Seoul with me?

278
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:25,553
No.

279
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:27,387
Why?

280
00:22:27,387 --> 00:22:29,420
Because of Ah Reum?

281
00:22:34,387 --> 00:22:36,553
His birth wasn't registered,

282
00:22:36,553 --> 00:22:39,620
and only a note with his name and age was left.

283
00:22:40,453 --> 00:22:43,053
Just leave him to an orphanage.

284
00:22:43,587 --> 00:22:46,520
How can she abandon a
child at a motel and leave?

285
00:22:49,453 --> 00:22:51,620
Well…

286
00:22:53,987 --> 00:22:56,587
In that letter…

287
00:22:57,820 --> 00:23:01,887
The letter said they would
come to find the child,

288
00:23:01,887 --> 00:23:07,087
so would it be alright if I keep him for now?

289
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:09,787
Then, please go ahead and do that.

290
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:14,920
What's your name?

291
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:16,720
Cha Seung Eon.

292
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:19,420
From now on, you're my sibling.

293
00:23:21,487 --> 00:23:25,053
Because my mom said she would come to get me.

294
00:23:25,053 --> 00:23:27,320
I have to wait.

295
00:23:28,120 --> 00:23:31,487
But I can't remember Mom's face.

296
00:23:33,553 --> 00:23:36,720
I can't even go to look for her.

297
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:40,353
So, I can't leave here, Kang Hee.

298
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:44,420
You don't have a picture of your mom?

299
00:24:11,887 --> 00:24:17,653
Your mom once said that I could call her 'mom.'

300
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:23,353
That's right.

301
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:29,553
My mom loved you more than me.

302
00:24:30,953 --> 00:24:32,620
I remember this day.

303
00:24:32,620 --> 00:24:34,753
It was the entrance ceremony.

304
00:24:34,753 --> 00:24:38,020
Even though it was the ceremony,
Mom didn't come to school

305
00:24:38,020 --> 00:24:41,053
and instead asked to take
pictures in front of the house.

306
00:24:41,687 --> 00:24:44,887
So I threw a tantrum and
didn't take the picture.

307
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:53,520
I should've taken it.

308
00:24:54,353 --> 00:24:56,420
I'll give it to you.

309
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:05,987
It's yours, isn't it?

310
00:25:08,620 --> 00:25:10,653
My mom's photo…

311
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:16,087
Thank you for keeping it so long.

312
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:21,687
And I'm sorry, Seung Eon.

313
00:25:58,120 --> 00:25:59,253
Good morning.

314
00:25:59,253 --> 00:26:01,520
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes.

315
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:03,887
You were going to Seoul without even
saying goodbye to me, weren't you?

316
00:26:03,887 --> 00:26:07,053
No, I was just about to go say goodbye now.

317
00:26:07,053 --> 00:26:08,953
You were?

318
00:26:12,153 --> 00:26:16,420
I didn't know the manager worked that much.

319
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:21,153
I was able to focus on the field
thanks to the manager.

320
00:26:21,153 --> 00:26:23,487
Tell me honestly.

321
00:26:23,487 --> 00:26:25,053
Yes.

322
00:26:25,053 --> 00:26:28,720
Did your heart waver even a little
when you were proposed to?

323
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:31,920
Of course, it wavered.

324
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:33,787
My mental state was

325
00:26:33,787 --> 00:26:35,487
completely shattered.

326
00:26:35,487 --> 00:26:37,920
If you don't come quickly, I'll make
a public proposal like that too.

327
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:40,087
You think I'd be scared?

328
00:26:40,087 --> 00:26:42,420
I'll make a public proposal to you too.

329
00:26:42,420 --> 00:26:44,520
To the whole world.

330
00:26:45,187 --> 00:26:47,087
I'm sorry.

331
00:26:50,820 --> 00:26:52,253
Manager.

332
00:26:52,253 --> 00:26:56,087
Do you know the order for the sinks
and sanitary ware is all wrong?

333
00:26:57,020 --> 00:26:58,687
Then you do it again.

334
00:26:58,687 --> 00:27:02,653
That's your work, so you handle it.

335
00:27:02,653 --> 00:27:04,287
There are hotel suppliers, right?

336
00:27:04,287 --> 00:27:07,820
Call them all up and check for products
that can meet the delivery schedule,

337
00:27:07,820 --> 00:27:09,687
compare the specifications, make a list,

338
00:27:09,687 --> 00:27:11,453
negotiate the prices, and place the orders.

339
00:27:11,453 --> 00:27:15,653
Yes, do that, Ms. Kang Hee.

340
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:18,520
If it's because of the proposal…

341
00:27:18,520 --> 00:27:20,687
Right, the proposal.

342
00:27:21,587 --> 00:27:23,987
I did that, too.

343
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:31,220
Is it because of Esther, by any chance?

344
00:27:32,487 --> 00:27:33,653
How do you know, Ms. Kang Hee?

345
00:27:33,653 --> 00:27:35,853
How did you know, manager?

346
00:27:35,853 --> 00:27:38,320
Something seemed off about that
guy, so I did a little investigation.

347
00:27:38,320 --> 00:27:41,853
And it turns out she wasn't his
cousin, but a woman he lived with.

348
00:27:41,853 --> 00:27:47,820
Then, was it all because of that, the silence
and strange behavior when you came last time?

349
00:27:47,820 --> 00:27:49,487
Is it not because I rejected your proposal?

350
00:27:49,487 --> 00:27:53,153
What's the big deal about
a proposal? I can just do that again.

351
00:27:53,153 --> 00:27:56,020
You are not getting married right away either.

352
00:27:56,020 --> 00:27:58,020
Esther even had a baby,

353
00:27:58,020 --> 00:27:59,920
but because her father is such a punk,

354
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:03,487
I can't just say let's raise
Little Heart without a father.

355
00:28:04,987 --> 00:28:08,187
I can't say it because I'm
afraid she might be shocked.

356
00:28:08,187 --> 00:28:10,487
Esther already knows everything.

357
00:28:10,487 --> 00:28:12,553
She was already shocked

358
00:28:12,553 --> 00:28:15,253
and saw it with her own eyes.

359
00:28:17,187 --> 00:28:19,520
Is Esther okay?

360
00:28:20,053 --> 00:28:22,287
Hey, Cheon Yeon Soo.

361
00:28:23,220 --> 00:28:24,453
Is it you?

362
00:28:24,453 --> 00:28:25,587
It's you, right?

363
00:28:25,587 --> 00:28:28,820
- What?
- Were you the one who talked to Min Jung?

364
00:28:29,287 --> 00:28:31,087
- It wasn't me.
- What do you mean it wasn't?

365
00:28:31,087 --> 00:28:33,587
She called the hospital
and found out my number.

366
00:28:33,587 --> 00:28:34,920
It's Ms. Yoon.

367
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:38,220
Ms. Yoon, you received it, right?

368
00:28:38,220 --> 00:28:42,087
Yes, well… I'm sorry.

369
00:28:42,087 --> 00:28:44,787
No, it's alright.

370
00:28:48,020 --> 00:28:50,387
Would Ms. Yoon have answered
the phone? Of course, it was me.

371
00:28:50,387 --> 00:28:52,453
Jeez.

372
00:28:52,453 --> 00:28:54,320
Why? What did Ms. Min Jung say?

373
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:55,453
She said she's coming.

374
00:28:55,453 --> 00:28:57,120
Really? Why?

375
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:59,053
I don't know.

376
00:28:59,053 --> 00:29:02,287
No, what if Min Jung asks me to try again

377
00:29:02,287 --> 00:29:04,553
and go to Seoul together?

378
00:29:04,553 --> 00:29:05,587
That won't happen.

379
00:29:05,587 --> 00:29:08,320
How do you know her feelings?

380
00:29:08,320 --> 00:29:11,053
Yeon Soo, save me, please.

381
00:29:11,053 --> 00:29:12,053
What can I do?

382
00:29:12,053 --> 00:29:16,653
If I go crazy and follow Min Jung
to Seoul, hold me back.

383
00:29:16,653 --> 00:29:18,853
Since you talk about Ms. Min Jung,

384
00:29:18,853 --> 00:29:20,053
I miss Kang Hee.

385
00:29:20,053 --> 00:29:21,653
Kang Hee again?

386
00:29:21,653 --> 00:29:23,820
Can't you focus on me?

387
00:29:23,820 --> 00:29:26,087
Ms. Yoon, tomorrow…

388
00:29:26,087 --> 00:29:30,053
If you're not busy, can I take a break?

389
00:29:30,053 --> 00:29:32,987
Yes, there's nothing special tomorrow, yet.

390
00:29:32,987 --> 00:29:34,753
Is that so?

391
00:29:34,753 --> 00:29:38,453
Han Woo, you'll meet Min Jung,
and I'll go meet Kang Hee.

392
00:29:38,453 --> 00:29:40,053
Jeez, that disloyal punk.

393
00:29:40,053 --> 00:29:41,387
You were the first to sever ties, you know?

394
00:29:41,387 --> 00:29:43,053
Jeez, that grudge-holding punk.

395
00:29:43,053 --> 00:29:45,720
If things go well with Min Jung
and we meet again,

396
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,987
we can hang out together in
Seoul, maybe a double date.

397
00:29:47,987 --> 00:29:49,487
Trashy brat.

398
00:29:49,487 --> 00:29:52,553
Did Ms. Min Jung come to see Han Woo?

399
00:29:53,687 --> 00:29:55,620
Do you know her too? The one called Min Jung?

400
00:29:55,620 --> 00:29:58,020
Yeah, it's Han Woo's ex-girlfriend.

401
00:29:58,020 --> 00:30:02,220
They dated on the premise of marriage,
so I've seen her a few times too.

402
00:30:03,787 --> 00:30:05,653
Marriage…

403
00:30:06,453 --> 00:30:10,520
Senior Han Woo… How was his life in Seoul?

404
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:13,187
Because it's unimaginable.

405
00:30:13,187 --> 00:30:15,287
He was just exactly a finance guy.

406
00:30:15,287 --> 00:30:19,487
I really couldn't imagine he'd
leave everything and come back.

407
00:30:19,487 --> 00:30:24,687
Then he must have made a really big
decision to start the second act of his life.

408
00:30:24,687 --> 00:30:28,920
Isn't it wrong to give up impulsively?

409
00:30:29,387 --> 00:30:30,887
Try to stop him, Ah Reum.

410
00:30:30,887 --> 00:30:35,987
No, how can I do that? Min Jung knows me too.

411
00:30:35,987 --> 00:30:40,653
I guess they'll talk it out
and sort things well.

412
00:30:43,187 --> 00:30:44,887
Still, should I give him a call

413
00:30:44,887 --> 00:30:47,153
to check if he's doing well with her?

414
00:30:58,120 --> 00:30:59,953
Hey, where are you?

415
00:31:19,820 --> 00:31:21,920
Senior.

416
00:31:26,653 --> 00:31:28,353
I heard Chil Ddaeng is sick.

417
00:31:28,353 --> 00:31:30,053
What?

418
00:31:30,053 --> 00:31:32,087
Don't go.

419
00:31:33,187 --> 00:31:36,720
If you go to Seoul, who will
take care of Chil Ddaeng?

420
00:31:39,220 --> 00:31:43,053
Ms. Yoon, I'm not going.

421
00:31:43,053 --> 00:31:44,920
Pardon?

422
00:31:48,787 --> 00:31:52,287
Aren't you the veterinarian who
performed surgery on Chil Ddaeng?

423
00:31:52,287 --> 00:31:54,920
Oh, hello.

424
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:58,287
It's good to see you living well before I go.

425
00:31:58,287 --> 00:32:00,487
Take care.

426
00:32:00,487 --> 00:32:04,353
Congratulations on your marriage, sincerely.

427
00:32:05,087 --> 00:32:06,953
I'll get going.

428
00:32:20,753 --> 00:32:23,520
Let's go, you said Chil Ddaeng is very sick.

429
00:32:23,520 --> 00:32:25,387
Yes.

430
00:32:34,353 --> 00:32:35,687
Oh, right.

431
00:32:35,687 --> 00:32:38,320
Have you decided on a name for the donkey?

432
00:32:40,420 --> 00:32:43,020
Not yet.

433
00:32:43,020 --> 00:32:45,520
Do you have anything in mind?

434
00:32:47,153 --> 00:32:49,753
Donkey, something like that?

435
00:32:49,753 --> 00:32:51,853
- I'm sorry.
- Well…

436
00:32:51,853 --> 00:32:54,187
But is it okay for you to come out so suddenly?

437
00:32:54,187 --> 00:32:55,553
What about the hospital?

438
00:32:55,553 --> 00:32:59,087
Yes, it's okay.

439
00:34:07,020 --> 00:34:09,687
<i>I lost the doll.</i>

440
00:34:10,653 --> 00:34:13,187
<i>The doll is missing.</i>

441
00:34:15,053 --> 00:34:17,320
<i>The day my mother left…</i>

442
00:34:23,353 --> 00:34:25,353
<i>My doll.</i>

443
00:34:27,753 --> 00:34:29,653
<i>Please find it for me.</i>

444
00:34:41,220 --> 00:34:43,153
Are you already here?

445
00:34:43,653 --> 00:34:45,820
Oh dear.

446
00:34:45,820 --> 00:34:48,387
I'm sorry I'm not Kang Hee.

447
00:34:49,087 --> 00:34:50,953
No, come in.

448
00:34:50,953 --> 00:34:52,787
Why are you flustered?

449
00:34:52,787 --> 00:34:54,853
No, I'm not.

450
00:34:56,187 --> 00:34:58,020
Take a seat.

451
00:35:01,353 --> 00:35:03,487
Oh dear.

452
00:35:07,053 --> 00:35:11,687
You were quite hurt because
I was opposed it, weren't you?

453
00:35:12,420 --> 00:35:14,253
Yes.

454
00:35:14,253 --> 00:35:15,753
A little bit.

455
00:35:15,753 --> 00:35:17,953
Actually…

456
00:35:18,587 --> 00:35:23,420
I opposed the two of you
as Cheon Yeon Soo's father.

457
00:35:23,420 --> 00:35:26,153
You've been through a lot, haven't you?

458
00:35:26,153 --> 00:35:29,153
You should be happy.

459
00:35:29,153 --> 00:35:33,220
You ought to live your life.

460
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:35,753
As for me,

461
00:35:36,420 --> 00:35:39,820
I'm happy as long as Kang Hee is by my side.

462
00:35:40,553 --> 00:35:44,587
Kang Hee is my life, after all.

463
00:35:50,520 --> 00:35:52,953
Now, I'll

464
00:35:52,953 --> 00:35:56,120
talk to you as Kang Hee's father.

465
00:35:57,187 --> 00:36:00,120
If it were up to me,

466
00:36:01,253 --> 00:36:05,687
I'd ask you over and over

467
00:36:07,287 --> 00:36:09,953
to take good care of Kang Hee.

468
00:36:11,620 --> 00:36:14,487
Do you know how happy I was

469
00:36:14,487 --> 00:36:19,553
when you said you would go meet Kang Hee

470
00:36:21,420 --> 00:36:23,720
instead of me last Christmas?

471
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:25,820
- Really?
- No, I'm lying.

472
00:36:25,820 --> 00:36:27,620
Jeez.

473
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:35,087
Have I placed too much of a burden on you?

474
00:36:35,087 --> 00:36:38,420
No, not at all. Never.

475
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:43,287
It seems like Kang Hee's
memory was coming back.

476
00:36:43,287 --> 00:36:45,187
Yes.

477
00:36:45,187 --> 00:36:49,987
She even vaguely remembers fainting
and losing consciousness as a child.

478
00:36:56,720 --> 00:36:58,987
Thank you

479
00:36:58,987 --> 00:37:01,587
for being by her side.

480
00:37:11,953 --> 00:37:14,020
I'll get going now.

481
00:37:14,020 --> 00:37:15,987
Alright.

482
00:37:17,420 --> 00:37:19,920
- Take a rest.
- Yes.

483
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:23,187
Why is this rascal here, not
even recognizing his master?

484
00:37:23,187 --> 00:37:26,587
Why are you hitting him? I'm the owner.

485
00:37:28,287 --> 00:37:30,487
Is it your son, or your daughter?

486
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:07,887
Kang Hee.

487
00:38:13,253 --> 00:38:15,353
Isn't she at home?

488
00:38:27,887 --> 00:38:32,187
<i>[Deceased Mia Kim Tyler]</i>

489
00:38:39,187 --> 00:38:41,787
<i>Oh? Mom, you're awake.</i>

490
00:38:43,687 --> 00:38:45,520
<i>Kang Hee, bring your clothes too.</i>

491
00:38:45,520 --> 00:38:47,353
<i>Okay.</i>

492
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:52,020
<i>Mom.</i>

493
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:55,120
<i>Here it is.</i>

494
00:38:57,420 --> 00:39:00,320
<i>Mom, where are we going?</i>

495
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:01,487
<i>California.</i>

496
00:39:01,487 --> 00:39:02,987
<i>This is California too, isn't it?</i>

497
00:39:02,987 --> 00:39:05,587
<i>Not here, but where I grew up.</i>

498
00:39:05,587 --> 00:39:06,987
<i>Is it far from here?</i>

499
00:39:06,987 --> 00:39:08,353
<i>It is far.</i>

500
00:39:08,353 --> 00:39:10,353
<i>How far is it?</i>

501
00:39:10,353 --> 00:39:12,487
<i>You'll find out when you get there.</i>

502
00:39:34,753 --> 00:39:36,653
<i>Let's go in.</i>

503
00:40:59,387 --> 00:41:02,087
<i>I love you, Kang Hee.</i>

504
00:41:40,820 --> 00:41:42,953
<i>Mom.</i>

505
00:42:28,320 --> 00:42:30,087
<i>- Kang Hee.
- Kang Hee.</i>

506
00:42:30,087 --> 00:42:33,120
<i>- Ji Kang Hee.
- Ji Kang Hee.</i>

507
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:34,653
Where did she go?

508
00:42:34,653 --> 00:42:36,753
<i>- Kang Hee.
- Kang Hee.</i>

509
00:42:36,753 --> 00:42:38,620
<i>- Kang Hee.
- Kang Hee.</i>

510
00:42:38,620 --> 00:42:39,720
<i>- Kang Hee.
- Ji Kang Hee.</i>

511
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:40,987
<i>Kang Hee.</i>

512
00:42:40,987 --> 00:42:43,187
<i>Ji Kang Hee.</i>

513
00:42:43,187 --> 00:42:45,353
<i>Ji Kang Hee.</i>

514
00:42:46,720 --> 00:42:48,853
<i>Kang Hee.</i>

515
00:42:50,620 --> 00:42:54,487
<i>She's here. I found Kang Hee.</i>

516
00:42:55,253 --> 00:42:57,653
<i>Come quickly.</i>

517
00:42:57,653 --> 00:43:00,087
<i>Open your eyes.</i>

518
00:43:02,487 --> 00:43:05,053
<i>Try opening your eyes.</i>

519
00:43:05,053 --> 00:43:07,153
<i>Come quickly.</i>

520
00:43:07,153 --> 00:43:11,353
<i>Kang Hee, open your eyes.</i>

521
00:43:11,353 --> 00:43:14,453
<i>Please, try opening your eyes.</i>

522
00:43:24,153 --> 00:43:26,353
<i>Mom.</i>

523
00:43:30,253 --> 00:43:33,453
<i>Mom, I'm sorry.</i>

524
00:44:07,187 --> 00:44:09,020
Kang Hee.

525
00:44:10,187 --> 00:44:14,387
Why are you here now? It's cold,
and you didn't answer your phone.

526
00:44:18,253 --> 00:44:20,453
Why did you come without saying anything?

527
00:44:20,453 --> 00:44:23,087
I came out to pick you up.

528
00:44:23,087 --> 00:44:27,187
I was worried, wondering if our paths
had crossed or if something had happened.

529
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:32,153
You just go first.

530
00:44:32,153 --> 00:44:34,353
What about you?

531
00:44:34,353 --> 00:44:36,320
Aren't you going?

532
00:44:41,387 --> 00:44:43,653
Should I sleep over then go?

533
00:44:48,053 --> 00:44:50,187
Let's break up.

534
00:44:52,620 --> 00:44:55,987
Let's break up now.

535
00:45:00,687 --> 00:45:02,453
Are you not feeling well?

536
00:45:02,453 --> 00:45:04,287
Just go.

537
00:45:05,120 --> 00:45:07,320
Kang Hee.

538
00:45:07,320 --> 00:45:09,287
Ji Kang Hee.

539
00:45:11,987 --> 00:45:13,853
Look at me.

540
00:45:18,587 --> 00:45:21,720
I don't know what's going on

541
00:45:21,720 --> 00:45:25,153
but if you need some time alone, I'll wait.

542
00:45:26,353 --> 00:45:29,353
When you want to talk about it later,

543
00:45:29,820 --> 00:45:31,987
tell me then.

544
00:45:37,420 --> 00:45:40,320
Don't struggle too long, Kang Hee.

545
00:45:42,020 --> 00:45:43,920
You understand, right?

546
00:47:20,387 --> 00:47:22,920
- Everything's been taken care of.
- Yes.

547
00:47:23,453 --> 00:47:26,887
Are you ready to be the ferry for the elderly

548
00:47:26,887 --> 00:47:28,820
who cannot cross the river?

549
00:47:28,820 --> 00:47:31,787
The ferry is ready.

550
00:47:33,020 --> 00:47:35,387
- Is everything ready?
- Yes.

551
00:47:35,387 --> 00:47:36,587
Well, then…

552
00:47:36,587 --> 00:47:41,353
Let's become a walking cane
for elders who can't walk.

553
00:47:45,920 --> 00:47:48,487
Oh my, you look so pretty.

554
00:47:48,487 --> 00:47:49,720
Did you put on makeup?

555
00:47:49,720 --> 00:47:53,553
Why would I wear makeup when I'm not even dead?

556
00:47:54,120 --> 00:47:57,287
No, I mean you look so lovely.

557
00:47:57,287 --> 00:47:58,887
He said you look so pretty.

558
00:47:58,887 --> 00:48:02,987
Are you telling me to die peacefully
and be cremated nicely?

559
00:48:02,987 --> 00:48:06,587
How can you say that?

560
00:48:16,520 --> 00:48:19,687
Take a picture of me too.

561
00:48:21,353 --> 00:48:23,253
- A funeral portrait?
- Yes.

562
00:48:23,253 --> 00:48:25,053
It would be better to
prepare it well in advance.

563
00:48:25,053 --> 00:48:27,853
Why would you already
prepare a funeral portrait?

564
00:48:27,853 --> 00:48:31,353
No, it's a photo for Kang Hee
to cherish for a long time,

565
00:48:31,353 --> 00:48:34,087
so I have to take one while
I'm at my best like this.

566
00:48:34,087 --> 00:48:37,987
Today is the most splendid and
wonderful day for me, isn't it?

567
00:48:37,987 --> 00:48:41,853
You should take a really cool
shot of me at this moment.

568
00:48:41,853 --> 00:48:43,687
Come on.

569
00:48:52,853 --> 00:48:54,787
Alright.

570
00:48:55,853 --> 00:48:57,387
What are you waiting for?

571
00:48:57,387 --> 00:48:58,520
Quick, take a picture!

572
00:48:58,520 --> 00:49:00,687
One, two, three, Motel California!

573
00:49:00,687 --> 00:49:03,587
Yay, go for it!

574
00:49:05,487 --> 00:49:07,587
What?

575
00:49:07,587 --> 00:49:10,553
Does the photo look bad? Is something on me?

576
00:49:11,387 --> 00:49:13,220
No.

577
00:49:13,820 --> 00:49:18,853
You look your best today.

578
00:49:18,853 --> 00:49:21,153
- I'll take it.
- Give it a shot, then.

579
00:49:21,153 --> 00:49:23,520
One, two, three, ready.

580
00:49:25,453 --> 00:49:30,120
One, two, three.

581
00:49:35,020 --> 00:49:37,820
<i>♪ Perhaps ♪</i>

582
00:49:37,820 --> 00:49:40,353
<i>♪ Perhaps I ♪</i>

583
00:49:40,353 --> 00:49:45,553
<i>♪ Won't be going to heaven ♪</i>

584
00:49:45,553 --> 00:49:53,387
<i>♪ Because my fear of heights is too severe ♪</i>

585
00:49:55,453 --> 00:50:00,020
<i>♪ Perhaps I, perhaps I ♪</i>

586
00:50:00,020 --> 00:50:04,853
<i>♪ Won't be going to heaven ♪</i>

587
00:50:04,853 --> 00:50:12,453
<i>♪ Because my pocket of greed is too heavy ♪</i>

588
00:50:14,320 --> 00:50:19,053
<i>♪ All night outside the window ♪</i>

589
00:50:19,053 --> 00:50:24,720
<i>♪ The sound of the heavy rain ♪</i>

590
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:34,353
Daughter, this is a song I've been
practicing lately, listen.

591
00:50:34,853 --> 00:50:40,153
<i>♪ Sipping one cup ♪</i>

592
00:50:40,153 --> 00:50:44,753
<i>♪ Then two cups of makgeolli ♪</i>

593
00:50:44,753 --> 00:50:52,287
<i>♪ I finally fell asleep when morning came ♪</i>

594
00:50:53,953 --> 00:50:56,020
How is it?

595
00:51:24,820 --> 00:51:26,753
Daughter.

596
00:51:28,553 --> 00:51:30,053
Sorry.

597
00:51:30,053 --> 00:51:32,153
What for?

598
00:51:32,153 --> 00:51:33,920
Why are you sorry?

599
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:37,153
I…

600
00:51:38,753 --> 00:51:41,753
I'm sorry for everything.

601
00:51:46,587 --> 00:51:48,987
Mr. Chun Pil,

602
00:51:49,953 --> 00:51:52,953
do you know what I can never forgive you?

603
00:51:56,220 --> 00:51:58,787
Why was I born?

604
00:52:00,420 --> 00:52:03,420
Both you and Mom

605
00:52:03,420 --> 00:52:05,787
didn't want me, right?

606
00:52:06,353 --> 00:52:08,853
That's really harsh.

607
00:52:10,553 --> 00:52:15,787
Where in the world is there
such a stupid question?

608
00:52:17,087 --> 00:52:20,020
Jeez.

609
00:52:20,020 --> 00:52:21,487
I… hey, you…

610
00:52:21,487 --> 00:52:27,620
It was back when indie bands were really
popular in front of Hongdae, that time.

611
00:52:27,620 --> 00:52:29,053
Huh?

612
00:52:29,053 --> 00:52:34,587
I gave up all those bands I liked
and came down to my hometown.

613
00:52:34,587 --> 00:52:37,720
To go all in for you and Mom.

614
00:52:39,153 --> 00:52:41,520
Wasn't it because you gave up
studying for the civil service exam?

615
00:52:41,520 --> 00:52:44,453
No, that's what people think.

616
00:52:44,453 --> 00:52:49,420
That kind of thing was not for me.

617
00:52:51,120 --> 00:52:54,953
Then you should have gone all in for Mom.

618
00:52:55,720 --> 00:53:00,553
So in my life, that was the biggest…

619
00:53:02,087 --> 00:53:06,220
The biggest mistake.

620
00:53:06,220 --> 00:53:10,487
Taking Mom away from you, that was all…

621
00:53:10,487 --> 00:53:14,087
So I'm really sorry about that.

622
00:53:15,420 --> 00:53:17,553
I totally hate it.

623
00:53:18,887 --> 00:53:22,087
This soft and mushy atmosphere.

624
00:53:22,087 --> 00:53:25,187
It feels like I need to forgive
something, make amends,

625
00:53:25,187 --> 00:53:28,453
and confess all my sins,
this kind of atmosphere…

626
00:53:28,453 --> 00:53:30,453
Don't force it.

627
00:53:31,287 --> 00:53:34,053
I love this kind of atmosphere.

628
00:53:34,053 --> 00:53:36,853
You are very spirited.

629
00:53:36,853 --> 00:53:39,887
Until I accept the apology,

630
00:53:40,687 --> 00:53:43,187
until I apologize,

631
00:53:45,487 --> 00:53:48,153
live long and healthily.

632
00:53:50,487 --> 00:53:53,753
I like it because you are always
the same, my daughter.

633
00:54:04,787 --> 00:54:07,587
Su Ji.

634
00:54:08,453 --> 00:54:10,853
Su Ji.

635
00:54:10,853 --> 00:54:14,187
Su Ji.

636
00:54:16,687 --> 00:54:18,553
I'm here.

637
00:54:18,553 --> 00:54:20,387
Oh.

638
00:54:20,853 --> 00:54:23,653
Where have you been?

639
00:54:24,187 --> 00:54:26,453
I was here in this flower garden.

640
00:54:26,453 --> 00:54:31,120
Now, Su Ji, you can't be in the flower garden.

641
00:54:31,120 --> 00:54:33,320
Oh, why not?

642
00:54:33,320 --> 00:54:38,387
That's because I can't find you, Su Ji.

643
00:54:38,387 --> 00:54:43,920
Can you really not tell the difference
between me and a flower?

644
00:54:43,920 --> 00:54:47,720
Oh, just a moment.

645
00:54:48,520 --> 00:54:50,120
<i>Hello, it's Kang Hee.</i>

646
00:54:50,120 --> 00:54:52,220
Gosh, you startled me.

647
00:54:52,220 --> 00:54:54,687
Who was that on the phone that surprised you?

648
00:54:54,687 --> 00:54:56,953
There's someone

649
00:54:56,953 --> 00:55:01,853
I said something I shouldn't have to.

650
00:55:02,753 --> 00:55:06,187
I should say sorry when we meet.

651
00:55:07,687 --> 00:55:11,053
I can't do that.

652
00:55:47,520 --> 00:55:51,287
Why are you doing this?

653
00:55:52,287 --> 00:55:55,253
I'm sorry, ma'am.

654
00:55:57,787 --> 00:55:59,687
Is this…

655
00:56:00,420 --> 00:56:01,853
Why are you doing this to me?

656
00:56:01,853 --> 00:56:07,487
I'm sorry for making you
uncomfortable all this time.

657
00:56:08,987 --> 00:56:10,687
I sincerely apologize to you.

658
00:56:10,687 --> 00:56:12,720
Apologize?

659
00:56:13,320 --> 00:56:15,653
What on earth are you up to?

660
00:56:15,653 --> 00:56:17,153
I just want to leave.

661
00:56:17,153 --> 00:56:19,220
I'll get going.

662
00:56:19,853 --> 00:56:21,853
The jujube tea here is tasty.

663
00:56:21,853 --> 00:56:23,987
Please have some before you go.

664
00:56:39,620 --> 00:56:41,953
Why is she acting like that?

665
00:57:08,320 --> 00:57:10,220
You are here?

666
00:57:12,387 --> 00:57:14,387
I have something to say.

667
00:57:15,487 --> 00:57:17,387
Me too.

668
00:57:18,720 --> 00:57:20,787
I also have something to say.

669
00:57:22,620 --> 00:57:24,653
Shall we go down?

670
00:57:25,387 --> 00:57:27,420
Yes.

671
00:57:40,920 --> 00:57:42,387
Yeon Soo, we…

672
00:57:42,387 --> 00:57:43,887
No.

673
00:57:43,887 --> 00:57:47,553
I think I know what you're
going to say, Kang Hee.

674
00:57:47,553 --> 00:57:48,587
Don't say that.

675
00:57:48,587 --> 00:57:50,853
Cheon Yeon Soo.

676
00:57:50,853 --> 00:57:53,153
You have to listen to me.

677
00:57:54,253 --> 00:57:57,153
From now on, the words I say…

678
00:57:57,153 --> 00:57:59,120
I'll start first.

679
00:57:59,587 --> 00:58:01,587
I'll start speaking first.

680
00:58:03,087 --> 00:58:05,353
Honestly,

681
00:58:06,153 --> 00:58:09,387
I had a lot on my mind after leaving
you alone in Seoul that day

682
00:58:10,020 --> 00:58:12,520
when you were struggling.

683
00:58:15,087 --> 00:58:18,120
I was thinking, 'What if you
say let's break up again,'

684
00:58:18,653 --> 00:58:21,920
'What if I'm told to wait more.'

685
00:58:21,920 --> 00:58:24,587
So I wondered if I should prepare myself.

686
00:58:27,687 --> 00:58:29,787
But you know what?

687
00:58:32,620 --> 00:58:35,387
I had already put down roots in you.

688
00:58:36,653 --> 00:58:41,687
If you hadn't been in my life, it would
have been as if I didn't exist either.

689
00:58:44,087 --> 00:58:46,887
My first goal in life was

690
00:58:46,887 --> 00:58:50,020
to become number one to you, Ji Kang Hee.

691
00:58:51,753 --> 00:58:53,987
And my first frustration was

692
00:58:56,620 --> 00:58:59,153
not being able to follow you to Seoul.

693
00:59:02,553 --> 00:59:06,087
You were also the first woman
who made me into a man,

694
00:59:07,920 --> 00:59:11,753
and you were the first person
I wanted to make happy.

695
00:59:16,520 --> 00:59:18,787
So what I'm saying is…

696
00:59:21,087 --> 00:59:24,420
You're not just my first love to me,

697
00:59:28,053 --> 00:59:30,720
but you're my everything, my beginning and end.

698
00:59:36,153 --> 00:59:38,420
I'm sorry for being too late.

699
00:59:42,953 --> 00:59:45,053
I love you.

700
00:59:46,920 --> 00:59:49,053
I love you, Kang Hee.

701
00:59:56,187 --> 00:59:58,553
You don't know

702
00:59:59,220 --> 01:00:02,020
when to use the words 'I love you', do you?

703
01:00:07,020 --> 01:00:09,453
After saying, 'I love you.'

704
01:00:10,120 --> 01:00:12,953
My mom told me she loved me,

705
01:00:13,720 --> 01:00:18,087
then took all my clothes out
and was planning to run away.

706
01:00:18,653 --> 01:00:21,153
Together with your dad.

707
01:00:25,953 --> 01:00:28,853
So, do you know what I did?

708
01:00:29,887 --> 01:00:32,587
I stuffed a teddy bear

709
01:00:33,620 --> 01:00:35,987
inside the car's exhaust pipe.

710
01:00:39,887 --> 01:00:41,887
What are you talking about?

711
01:00:41,887 --> 01:00:44,420
The car accident that day…

712
01:00:45,120 --> 01:00:47,387
I caused it.

713
01:00:49,553 --> 01:00:52,387
I killed my mom,

714
01:00:53,987 --> 01:00:56,187
and your dad.

715
01:00:59,553 --> 01:01:01,920
I'm the one who took your dad from you

716
01:01:01,920 --> 01:01:05,187
and took his wife from Mr. Chun Pil.

717
01:01:06,520 --> 01:01:08,753
I am a murderer.

718
01:01:19,600 --> 01:01:22,100
The words 'I love you'

719
01:01:25,753 --> 01:01:28,287
are what people say when they are leaving.

720
01:01:30,153 --> 01:01:32,187
Yeon Soo.

721
01:01:35,853 --> 01:01:38,120
So what I'm trying to say is…

722
01:01:42,353 --> 01:01:44,420
Don't say it.

723
01:01:47,753 --> 01:01:49,953
Please, don't say it.

724
01:01:54,520 --> 01:01:56,620
I love you.

725
01:02:03,620 --> 01:02:05,987
I love you, Yeon Soo.

726
01:02:40,387 --> 01:02:44,753
<i>[Motel California]</i>
